  "local_port": 34580,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can you check your WhatsApp from another phone?",
  "response": "Yes, you can check your WhatsApp messages from another phone by using WhatsApp Web or by linking another device with WhatsApp. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **WhatsApp Web:**\n   - Open a web browser on the other phone and go to the WhatsApp Web website (web.whatsapp.com).\n   - On your primary phone (the one where your WhatsApp account is active), open WhatsApp, tap the three dots in the upper right corner (on Android) or the settings tab (on iPhone).\n   - Select \"Linked Devices\" and then tap \"Link a Device.\"\n   - Use your phone to scan the QR code displayed on the other phone\u2019s browser.\n\n2. **WhatsApp Multi-device Beta:**\n   - If you\u2019ve opted into the Multi-device feature, you can use WhatsApp on different devices without needing to have your phone connected to the internet. However, your account will still be linked to your primary phone number.\n\nKeep in mind that for security reasons, WhatsApp does not support using your account on two phones simultaneously, but you can manage it via WhatsApp Web or by linking devices as mentioned above.",
